{
  "text": "Our results showed that more than 95 % of participants were not aware of PAD. Different levels of PAD awareness have been reported by previous populationbased studies in the United States (25 %) [CITATION_1] , Canada (36 %) [CITATION_2] and the Netherlands (<20 %) [CITATION_3] . Previous studies have also reported a significantly lower level of public awareness of PAD compared with other cardiovascular diseases such as CVA and coronary artery disease (60-75 %) [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . However, these previous studies were conducted in Europe or the United States and there are nopublished literatures on awareness of PAD in Asian countries.",
